<subSubSection id="48D355CA8E35FFBC48A75165FE2BFD1F" lastPageId="124" lastPageNumber="125" pageId="123" pageNumber="124" type="description">
<paragraph id="007606418E35FFBC48A75165FDD7FD3C" blockId="123.[151,1436,1609,2030]" lastBlockId="124.[151,1437,151,1292]" lastPageId="124" lastPageNumber="125" pageId="123" pageNumber="124">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E35FFBB48A75165FE0AF991" bold="true" box="[151,431,1609,1634]" pageId="123" pageNumber="124">Description of Female.</emphasis>
Fully winged; length 
<quantity id="C731ABA48E35FFBB4AF85165FCFDF991" box="[712,856,1609,1633]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.55" metricValueMax="2.7" metricValueMin="2.4" pageId="123" pageNumber="124" unit="mm" value="2.55" valueMax="2.7" valueMin="2.4">2.4–2.7 mm</quantity>
. Head black, except mandible, clypeus and gena yellow-whitish; face with anterior half yellow-whitish and posterior half black; vertex of head black; part of ventral side of head yellow. Occasionally temple testaceous. Antenna yellow-whitish. Prothorax black, except pronotal tubercle white or testaceous; occasionally posterior margin of pronotum brown-testaceous; occasionally pronotum with lateral regions of posterior surface testaceous. Mesothorax, metathorax and propodeum black. Occasionally lateral regions of scutum partly testaceous. Legs yellow-whitish. Petiole black. Metasoma black or brown. Antenna clavate; antennal segments of 
<typeStatus id="DF72B8E38E35FFBB49C7500DFDFCF8C9" box="[503,601,1825,1849]" pageId="123" pageNumber="124">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28E35FFBB4AB5500DFCB3F8C9" authorityName="Olmi" authorityYear="1984" box="[645,790,1825,1849]" class="Insecta" family="Dryinidae" genus="Anteon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="123" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lankanum">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E35FFBB4AB5500DFCB3F8C9" box="[645,790,1825,1849]" italics="true" pageId="123" pageNumber="124">A. lankanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in following proportions: 11:7:7:7:7:7:6:7:7:9; antennal segments of 
<typeStatus id="DF72B8E38E35FFBB491C5069FE2BF8AD" box="[300,398,1861,1885]" pageId="123" pageNumber="124">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28E35FFBB498B5069FD97F8AD" authorityName="Xu &amp; He" authorityYear="1999" box="[443,562,1861,1885]" class="Insecta" family="Dryinidae" genus="Anteon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="123" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="planum">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E35FFBB498B5069FD97F8AD" box="[443,562,1861,1885]" italics="true" pageId="123" pageNumber="124">A. planum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in following proportions: 5.5:3.3:3.3:3.3:3.0:3.0:3.0:3.0:3.0:5.2.Head shiny, punctate, unsculptured among punctures, with anterior half of face slightly rugose. Head hairless, except dense and long hairs on yellow frontal spot. In specimen from 
<collectingCountry id="78DE46D18E35FFBB4ADE50A1FC96F855" box="[750,819,1933,1957]" name="China" pageId="123" pageNumber="124">China</collectingCountry>
, Naban River National Nature Reserve, vertex behind ocellar triangle rugose. Frontal line incomplete. Occipital carina complete. Head of 
<typeStatus id="DF72B8E38E35FFBB4C7B509DFB08F839" box="[1099,1197,1969,1993]" pageId="123" pageNumber="124">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28E35FFBB4CE4509DFAC7F839" authorityName="Olmi" authorityYear="1984" box="[1236,1378,1969,1993]" class="Insecta" family="Dryinidae" genus="Anteon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="123" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lankanum">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E35FFBB4CE4509DFAC7F839" box="[1236,1378,1969,1993]" italics="true" pageId="123" pageNumber="124">A. lankanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with POL = 3; OL = 6; OOL = 5; OPL = 4; TL = 5; greatest breadth of the posterior ocelli shorter than OPL (2:4). Head of 
<typeStatus id="DF72B8E38E32FFBC488557BBFEB2FF5F" box="[181,279,151,175]" pageId="124" pageNumber="125">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28E32FFBC490C57B4FE0BFF40" authorityName="Xu &amp; He" authorityYear="1999" box="[316,430,152,176]" class="Insecta" family="Dryinidae" genus="Anteon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="124" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="planum">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E32FFBC490C57B4FE0BFF40" box="[316,430,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="124" pageNumber="125">A. planum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with POL = 1.5; OL = 3.0; OOL = 3.0; OPL = 2.3; TL = 3.5; greatest breadth of posterior ocelli shorter than OPL (1:2.3). In specimen from 
<collectingCountry id="78DE46D18E32FFBC4AF55790FCAFFF24" box="[709,778,188,212]" name="China" pageId="124" pageNumber="125">China</collectingCountry>
, Nanling National Nature Reserve, POL = 3; OL = 5; OOL = 3.5; OPL = 3; TL = 5; greatest breadth of posterior ocelli slightly shorter than OPL (2.5:3). Pronotum shiny, hairy, punctate, unsculptured among punctures, rugose near anterior margin; pronotal tubercle reaching tegula. Pronotum slightly longer than scutum (14:11). Scutum, scutellum and metanotum shiny, smooth, punctate, unsculptured among punctures. Notauli incomplete, reaching 0.65–0.70 length of scutum. Propodeum with transverse keel between dorsal and posterior surfaces; posterior surface with two longitudinal keels, with median area sculptured by several slight striae or keels and lateral areas reticulate rugose; dorsal surface of propodeum shorter than posterior surface (6:8). In specimen from 
<collectingCountry id="78DE46D18E32FFBC4AC7569BFC99FE3F" box="[759,828,439,463]" name="China" pageId="124" pageNumber="125">China</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="78DE46D18E32FFBC4B77569BFC39FE3F" box="[839,924,439,463]" name="Taiwan" pageId="124" pageNumber="125">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
, Meifeng, median area of posterior surface of propodeum partly smooth. In specimen from 
<collectingCountry id="78DE46D18E32FFBC4AF656F0FCA9FE04" box="[710,780,476,500]" name="China" pageId="124" pageNumber="125">China</collectingCountry>
, Mt. Yinggeling, median area of posterior surface of propodeum completely reticulate rugose. Fore wing hyaline, without dark transverse band; distal part of stigmal vein shorter than proximal part (4.5:10, or 2:6). Protarsal segments of 
<typeStatus id="DF72B8E38E32FFBC4BEE5508FBE5FDCC" box="[990,1088,548,572]" pageId="124" pageNumber="125">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28E32FFBC4C5F5508FAA4FDCC" authorityName="Olmi" authorityYear="1984" box="[1135,1281,548,572]" class="Insecta" family="Dryinidae" genus="Anteon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="124" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lankanum">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E32FFBC4C5F5508FAA4FDCC" box="[1135,1281,548,572]" italics="true" pageId="124" pageNumber="125">A. lankanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in following proportions: 9:3:3:9:19. Protarsal segments of 
<typeStatus id="DF72B8E38E32FFBC4B36556BFCCDFDAF" box="[774,872,583,607]" pageId="124" pageNumber="125">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28E32FFBC4B865564FB9BFD90" authorityName="Xu &amp; He" authorityYear="1999" box="[950,1086,584,608]" class="Insecta" family="Dryinidae" genus="Anteon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="124" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="planum">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E32FFBC4B865564FB9BFD90" box="[950,1086,584,608]" italics="true" pageId="124" pageNumber="125">A. planum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in following proportions: 4.0:1.3:1.5:5.3:10.0. Enlarged claw (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E32FFBC4A065540FD07FD74" box="[566,674,620,644]" captionStart="PLATE 32" captionStartId="122.[151,233,1880,1903]" captionTargetBox="[191,1401,215,1833]" captionTargetId="figure-98@122.[166,1421,195,1858]" captionTargetPageId="122" captionText="PLATE 32. A, B, E, F. Chelae, holotypes. C, D. Male genitalia. A. Anteon kresli (from Olmi 2008b). B. A. krombeini (from Olmi 1984). C. A. krombeini from Sri Lanka (from Olmi 1984). D. A. laeve, holotype (from Xu et al. 1998). E. A. laminatum (from Olmi 1987a). F. A. lankanum (from Olmi 1984). Scale bar 0.32 mm for A, 0.34 mm for B, 0.33 mm for C, 0.23 mm for D, 0.26 mm for E and F." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278488" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278488/files/figure.png" pageId="124" pageNumber="125">Plate 32F</figureCitation>
) with proximal prominence bearing one long bristle. Segment 5 of protarsus (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E32FFBC493E55A3FEDCFD57" box="[270,377,655,679]" captionStart="PLATE 32" captionStartId="122.[151,233,1880,1903]" captionTargetBox="[191,1401,215,1833]" captionTargetId="figure-98@122.[166,1421,195,1858]" captionTargetPageId="122" captionText="PLATE 32. A, B, E, F. Chelae, holotypes. C, D. Male genitalia. A. Anteon kresli (from Olmi 2008b). B. A. krombeini (from Olmi 1984). C. A. krombeini from Sri Lanka (from Olmi 1984). D. A. laeve, holotype (from Xu et al. 1998). E. A. laminatum (from Olmi 1987a). F. A. lankanum (from Olmi 1984). Scale bar 0.32 mm for A, 0.34 mm for B, 0.33 mm for C, 0.23 mm for D, 0.26 mm for E and F." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278488" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278488/files/figure.png" pageId="124" pageNumber="125">Plate 32F</figureCitation>
) with basal region much shorter than distal one, with two rows of 12–26 lamellae; distal apex with two–five lamellae. Tibial spurs 1/1/2.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="007606418E32FFBC48F755F4FE2BFD1F" blockId="124.[151,1437,151,1292]" box="[199,398,727,752]" pageId="124" pageNumber="125">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E32FFBC48F755F4FEAEFD00" bold="true" box="[199,267,728,752]" pageId="124" pageNumber="125">Male.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
