<subSubSection id="48D355CA8E32FFBC48F753A4FB3AFAFB" pageId="124" pageNumber="125" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="007606418E32FFBC48F753A4FB3AFAFB" blockId="124.[151,1437,151,1292]" pageId="124" pageNumber="125">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E32FFBC48F753A4FE9EFB50" bold="true" box="[199,315,1160,1184]" pageId="124" pageNumber="125">Remarks.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus id="DF72B8E38E32FFBC494453ABFE73FB6F" box="[372,470,1159,1183]" pageId="124" pageNumber="125">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28E32FFBC49CB53A4FDCBFB50" authorityName="Xu &amp; He" authorityYear="1999" box="[507,622,1160,1184]" class="Insecta" family="Dryinidae" genus="Anteon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="124" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="planum">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E32FFBC49CB53A4FDCBFB50" box="[507,622,1160,1184]" italics="true" pageId="124" pageNumber="125">A. planum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(only known specimen of this species) was a female deposited in 
<collectionCode id="66D89E848E32FFBC4D6253ABFA3CFB6F" box="[1362,1433,1159,1183]" pageId="124" pageNumber="125">ZJUC</collectionCode>
. However, presently it is lost. In 2005 we examined a pin with the original labels, but with no glued specimens. According to Professor Zaifu Xu, this 
<typeStatus id="DF72B8E38E32FFBC4A7E53E3FD15FB17" box="[590,688,1231,1255]" pageId="124" pageNumber="125">holotype</typeStatus>
is lost, because it was destroyed by Psocoptera. According to the original description, there are no doubts that 
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28E32FFBC4ABD53D8FCA5FAFC" authorityName="Xu &amp; He" authorityYear="1999" box="[653,768,1268,1292]" class="Insecta" family="Dryinidae" genus="Anteon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="124" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="planum">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E32FFBC4ABD53D8FCA5FAFC" box="[653,768,1268,1292]" italics="true" pageId="124" pageNumber="125">A. planum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28E32FFBC4C3A53D8FB32FAFC" authorityName="Olmi" authorityYear="1984" box="[1034,1175,1268,1292]" class="Insecta" family="Dryinidae" genus="Anteon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="124" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lankanum">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E32FFBC4C3A53D8FB32FAFC" box="[1034,1175,1268,1292]" italics="true" pageId="124" pageNumber="125">A. lankanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
